&lt;p&gt;Fixed term or secondment opportunity for Band 6 Paediatric Physiotherapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Paediatric Physiotherapist to join our experienced team of physiotherapists at Chailey Clinical Services. We work within a multidisciplinary team to provide physiotherapy for children and young people with complex neurodisabilities. This includes services to pupils attending Chailey Heritage Foundation School, residences, Futures young adults&#39; service, the Chailey Rehabilitation and Transition Service, and outpatient clinic services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic person with excellent communication skills. Experience of working in paediatrics or with young adults is desirable, but a full induction and in-service training programme is available to support development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be full time, 37.5 hours per week for 12 months on a fixed term contract from 1 January 2021 to 31 December 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah CrombieJob titleAdvanced Clinical Practitioner and Physiotherapy Team LeadEmail addresssarah.crombie@nhs.netTelephone number01825 722112&lt;/p&gt;
